text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Maryland was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. SenatorKamala Harris had won 10 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:21st century in Maryland
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Maryland
